      <div resp="part:emfr" type="translation">
        <p n="1">Prosperity! Fortune!</p>
        <p n="1-2">Fifteenth year.</p>
        <p n="2-8"></p>
        <p n="8-11"></p>
        <p n="11-12"></p>
        <p n="12-14">These fourteen <foreign>kāṭi</foreign>s, We have taken them, We ... Ci<supplied reason="lost">va</supplied> <gap reason="lost"></gap></p>
      </div>
      <div type="commentary">
        <p>The inscription is incomplete. <ptr target="bib:Mahalingam1988_01"></ptr> notes: <quote>Probably a few more letters are wanting. The significance of these names is not clear. They were probably the <hi rend="italic">taḷi uḍaiyār</hi> (temple priests), as stated in l. 13.</quote></p>
        <p>According to <ptr target="bib:Mahalingam1988_01"></ptr>: <quote>This gives the earliest reference to the setting up of the image of god Ganapati, during the Pallava period.</quote></p>
      </div>
